"DateUtils.truncate" from Apache Commons Lang library should not be used
The use of the ZonedDateTime class introduced in Java 8 to truncate a date can be significantly faster than the DateUtils class from Commons Lang. Note that this rule is automatically disabled when the projectâ€™s sonar.java.source is lower than 8. 
### Noncompliant
public Date trunc(Date date) {
  return DateUtils.truncate(date, Calendar.SECOND);  // Noncompliant
}
 
### Compliant
public Date trunc(Date date) {
  Instant instant = date.toInstant();
  ZonedDateTime zonedDateTime = instant.atZone(ZoneId.systemDefault());
  ZonedDateTime truncatedZonedDateTime = zonedDateTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);
  Instant truncatedInstant = truncatedZonedDateTime.toInstant();
  return Date.from(truncatedInstant);
}
### Noncompliant
